data.name: lblInfo.Text
data.value: This wizard will bring you through the process of create a locally published software package. You must select an MSI, MSP, or EXE file as the update file. If the EXE file has an embedded MSI file then you must enter the relative path. If there are other supporting files needed, such as transform files, then use the additional files list to add them.

data.name: lblPackageInfo.Text
data.value: Enter the relevant details about the software package here. Refer to the documentation for questions regarding individual fields.

data.name: isInstalledRules.Instructions
data.value: Use this form to create, edit, remove, and group rules that determine if this software package is already installed. If you created this update using an MSI or MSP file you will see the automatically generated rule at the installable item level. By default the rules are in an AND group.

data.name: isInstallableRules.Instructions
data.value: Use this form to create, edit, remove, and group rules that determine if this software package can be installed. If you created this update using an MSI or MSP file you will see the automatically generated rule at the installable item level. By default the rules are in an AND group.

data.name: lblIsSuperseded.Text
data.value: This form lists the rules that determine if the software package is superseded. If you created this update using a MSI or MSP file you will see the automatically generated rule at the installable item level.

data.name: lblMetaData.Text
data.value: Use this form to review the metadata used by the previous is installable, is installed, or is superseded rules.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value: Use this form to review the XML data that will be used to describe the software package. Select Finish to publish this package to the WSUS server.
